"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447508","Department of Health","false","2016-01-29","<p>NHS England is an independent body established by the Health and Social Care Act 2012. Its Chief Executive, Simon Stevens, can make public policy statements. There are no plans to review this.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-01-29T11:59:40.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447508/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447508/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447508/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-25","NHS England","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they have any plans to review the powers of the Chief Executive of NHS England in terms of making public policy statements.","false","Biography information for Lord Scriven",,"Lord Scriven","HL5410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447510","Department for Education","false","2016-01-29","<p>A record of each headteacher board meeting is published on a monthly basis, with a two month delay prior to publication.</p><p>Since October 2015 these records have been made more detailed, reflecting a desire to increase transparency, whilst maintaining the integrity of the board discussions.</p><p>All published records of headteacher board meetings are available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/schools-commissioners-group/about/our-governance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/schools-commissioners-group/about/our-governance</a></p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2016-01-29T13:26:08.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447510/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447510/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447510/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-01-25","Headteacher Boards","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they are taking to ensure that the minutes of headteacher board meetings are sufficiently detailed and transparent for the benefit of parents and other stakeholders.","false","Biography information for Lord Storey",,"Lord Storey","HL5412"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447511","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-02-02","<p>We have not had any discussions with the Israeli authorities on this specific issue. We consistently urge Israel to ease movement and access restrictions across the Occupied Palestinian Territories, not least because of the impact the restrictions have on children and their education. Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv also regularly raise our concerns with the Israeli government officials about the imprisonment of Palestinians outside the West Bank, in direct contravention of Article 76 of the Fourth Geneva Convention.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-02-02T16:58:02.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447511/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447511/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447511/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-25","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with the government of Israel concerning the students from Birzeit university who are currently in prison; and what assessment they have made of the government of Israel’s treatment of Palestinian students.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL5413"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447512","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-02-04","We have not had any discussions with the Israeli authorities on this specific issue. However, we remain concerned about the high number of criminal investigations into fatal shootings of Palestinians that are closed without indictments. Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv regularly meet senior Israeli officials in the Ministry of Justice, Attorney General’s Office, Military Advocate General’s office, State Comptroller, National Security Council and other government bodies to lobby on this issue.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-02-04T16:53:50.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447512/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447512/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447512/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-25","Samir Awad","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with the government of Israel concerning the charges brought against those convicted of the killing of Samir Awad.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL5414"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447513","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-02-04","<p>We have not made representations on this specific issue to the Israeli authorities but are aware of the dire situation in this Palestinian village in the northern Jordan Valley area of the West Bank. We regularly raise the issue of water in the Occupied Palestinian Territories with the Israeli authorities, stressing the urgent need for Israel to improve this unacceptable situation and ensure fair distribution of water in the West Bank and Gaza.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-02-04T17:15:00.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447513/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447513/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447513/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-25","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel concerning the claim by a resident in Bardala that the Israeli army and water company have taken their water and are selling it back to villagers.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL5415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447514","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-02-04","<p>We have not made representations on this specific issue to the Israeli authorities. We do, however, regularly raise our concerns with the Israeli authorities over demolitions and settler violence. We understand that during the most recent olive harvesting season destruction was at a lower level than previous years due to stronger coordination between the Israel Defence Forces and Palestinian local authorities. Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv met Israeli government and community leaders to urge them to take action and speak out against settler violence.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-02-04T17:06:30.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447514/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447514/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447514/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-25","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel regarding the demolition of a Palestinian tree nursery by the Israel Defence Forces that had previously been robbed by Israeli settlers.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL5416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447515","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-02-04","Our Embassy in Tel Aviv has been following this case and we now understand that Nasser Nawaj’ah has been released. However, we remain concerned about Israel’s extensive use of administrative detention which, according to international law, should be used only when security makes it absolutely necessary rather than as routine practice, and as a preventive rather than a punitive measure. Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv most recently raised this matter on 3 November 2015 with Israeli officials from the Ministry of Justice, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the Office of the Deputy Attorney General.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-02-04T17:05:48.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447515/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447515/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447515/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-25","Nasser Nawaj'a","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel following the arrest and detention of Nasser Nawaj’a.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL5417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447516","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-02-04","<p>The Government has not raised Mr Abu Sakha’s particular case with the Israeli authorities. However, we remain concerned about Israel’s extensive use of administrative detention which, according to international law, should be used only when security makes this absolutely necessary rather than as routine practice, and as a preventive rather than a punitive measure. Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv raised the issue most recently on 3 November 2015 with Israeli officials from the Ministry of Justice, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the Office of the Deputy Attorney General.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-02-04T17:05:13.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447516/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447516/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447516/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-25","Mohammad Faisal Abu Sakha","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel concerning the detention of Mohammad Faisal Abu Sakha.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL5418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447526","Home Office","false","2016-02-02","<p>The type of visa held by an individual is not gathered as part of the exit checks process at the point of departure. Exit checks data forms one part of the information that is held on an individual’s travel and can be compared to arrival and visa records.</p><p>Home Office statisticians are considering the use of the data collected for statistical reporting purposes, and plan to publish an initial report on 26 May 2016.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2016-02-02T14:45:52.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447526/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447526/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447526/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-01-25","Borders: Personal Records","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the category of visa held by a departing person is recorded when exit checks are undertaken at UK borders; and, if that data are collected, whether they will publish that data.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hamwee",,"Baroness Hamwee","HL5428"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447527","Home Office","false","2016-02-02","<p>The Government thanks the Migration Advisory Committee for its report. We are considering its findings carefully and will respond in due course.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2016-02-02T15:45:34.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447527/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447527/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447527/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-01-25","Visas: Migrant Workers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they will respond to the Migration Advisory Committee's review of Tier 2 migration published on 19 January.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hamwee",,"Baroness Hamwee","HL5429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447529","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-24","<p>The review of the UK unsafe product recall system chaired by Lynn Faulds Wood and the government response was published on the 18 February.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2016-02-24T17:21:28.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447529/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447529/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447529/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-25","Recall of Unsafe Products Review","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answers by Baroness Neville-Rolfe on 11 November 2015 (HL3158) and 13 January (HL4697), when they will publish the report of the review of unsafe product recall chaired by Lynn Faulds Wood and their response to it.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town",,"Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town","HL5431"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447532","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-02","<p>The Timber and Timber Products (Placing on the Market) Regulations 2013 provide for the use of a Notice placing obligations on companies to comply with requirements, breach of which is a criminal offence.</p><p> </p><p>Regulation 13 provides graduated penalties for offences: on summary conviction, a fine of £5000 and/or 3 months imprisonment; and on indictment, an unlimited fine and/or 2 years imprisonment.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2016-02-02T12:14:32.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447532/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447532/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447532/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-25","Timber: Smuggling","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what sanctions the National Measurement Office can take against companies that trade in illegally imported timber.","false","Biography information for Baroness Jones of Whitchurch",,"Baroness Jones of Whitchurch","HL5434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447533","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-04","<p>Emissions type approval of new vehicles in the UK is carried out at commercially operated laboratories. There are five of these, as well as approved laboratories at manufacturers’ premises. The Vehicle Certification Agency (VCA) manages the approval testing of vehicles in the UK.</p><p> </p><p>Additional testing which is currently being undertaken on the road uses portable emission measurement systems (PEMS). The VCA owns two PEMS kits and can hire three additional PEMS kits from the commercial laboratories.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-02-04T12:10:05.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447533/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447533/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447533/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-25","Motor Vehicles: Exhaust Emissions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many vehicle testing kits are available to the government agencies responsible for checking whether vehicles comply with EU emission standards.","false","Biography information for Baroness Jones of Whitchurch",,"Baroness Jones of Whitchurch","HL5435"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447534","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-02","<p>Further education is demand led. Training providers have the flexibility to offer courses that respond to local skills needs. However, Table 1 shows the number of further education enrolments in the Horticulture and Forestry Tier 2 Sector Subject Area (SSA) over the past five academic years.</p><p>Table 1: All Age Further Education Enrolments in the Horticulture and Forestry Sector Subject Area, 2010/11 to 2014/15</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Academic Year</p></td><td><p>Enrolments</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>36,200</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>37,200</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>45,400</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>46,300</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>41,600</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Notes</p><p>1. These figures are a count of all enrolments that have occurred at any point in the year. Where a learner enrols on multiple aims (courses), these will be counted separately, even those with the same aim title.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Further education is demand led. Training providers have the flexibility to offer courses that respond to local skills needs. However, Table 1 shows the number of further education enrolments in the Horticulture and Forestry Tier 2 Sector Subject Area (SSA) over the past five academic years.</p><p>Table 1: All Age Further Education Enrolments in the Horticulture and Forestry Sector Subject Area, 2010/11 to 2014/15</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Academic Year</p></td><td><p>Enrolments</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>36,200</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>37,200</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>45,400</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>46,300</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>41,600</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Notes</p><p>1. These figures are a count of all enrolments that have occurred at any point in the year. Where a learner enrols on multiple aims (courses), these will be counted separately, even those with the same aim title.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2016-02-02T16:09:08.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447534/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447534/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447534/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-25","Horticulture: Training","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many horticulture training places on further education courses were available in each of the last five academic years.","false","Biography information for Baroness Jones of Whitchurch",,"Baroness Jones of Whitchurch","HL5436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447535","Home Office","false","2016-02-02","<p>The Government fully understands the importance of tackling wildlife crime and the important contribution that the National Wildlife Crime Unit makes to this, both here in the UK and internationally. That is reflected in the fact that the Government is providing over £270,000 worth of specific funding to support the work of the Unit in 2015/16. As far as funding beyond March 2016 is concerned, a decision will be made in due course.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2016-02-02T15:33:07.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447535/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447535/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447535/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-01-25","National Wildlife Crime Unit","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the future of the UK National Wildlife Crime Unit.","false","Biography information for Baroness Jones of Whitchurch",,"Baroness Jones of Whitchurch","HL5437"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447538","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-02","<p>Overall outflow figures for the Future Reserve 2020 (FR20) Volunteer Reserve in 2015 have fallen compared with previous years, with this fall driven primarily by the Army Reserve. This reflects the impact of a number of initiatives we have taken to improve the Reserves experience, such as better equipment and training, improved reward, and wider opportunities to serve alongside the Regulars as well as improving our relationships with employers.</p><p> </p><p>Increases in outflow from the Maritime and RAF Reserves should be understood within the context of significant increases to their strengths over the period. As a proportion of their respective trained-strengths, outflow figures for the Maritime and RAF Reserves have been steady, and are sustainable and consistent with the FR20 programme and related targets. This is evidenced by the fact that the Maritime and RAF Reserves are currently above their April 2016 trained strength targets.</p><p> </p><p>The attached tables provide detailed information on FR20 outflow and trained strength since 2013.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-02-02T16:13:34.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447538/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447538/answer","HL5440 - FR20 Volunteer Reserve Outflow.docx ; HL5440 - FR20 Volunteer Reserve Trained Strength.docx","HL5440 - FR20 Volunteer Reserve Outflow.docx ; HL5440 - FR20 Volunteer Reserve Trained Strength.docx","HL5440 - Future Reserves 2020 Outflow ; HL5440 - Reserve Trained Strength","HL5440 - Future Reserves 2020 Outflow ; HL5440 - Reserve Trained Strength","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447538/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-25","Reserve Forces: Discharges","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the number of reservists leaving the (1) army, (2) Royal Navy, and (3) Royal Air Force, in 2015.","false","Biography information for Lord Touhig",,"Lord Touhig","HL5440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447540","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-02","<p>I refer the noble Lord to the answer given by my hon. Friend, the Minister for Reserves, in the House of Commons on 14 January 2016 to Question 21901.</p><p>http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-01-11/21901/</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-02-02T15:41:46.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447540/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447540/answer","Hansard Extract 14 January 2016 , HOC 21901.docx","Hansard Extract 14 January 2016 , HOC 21901.docx","Reserve Forces","Reserve Forces","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447540/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-25","Reserve Forces","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they are taking to ensure the retention of reservists in the Armed Forces.","false","Biography information for Lord Touhig",,"Lord Touhig","HL5442"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447541","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-02","<p>Data prior to April 2012 for the Future Reserve 2020 (FR20) Volunteer Reserve is unavailable. It is, therefore, not possible to estimate the average length of service for the FR20 Volunteer Reserve population.</p><p> </p><p>As an alternative, I refer the noble Lord to the answer I gave on 26 January 2016 to Question HL5059 to the noble Lord The Lord Empey, which sets out details of FR20 Volunteer Reserve strength retention.</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Lords/2016-01-14/HL5059/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Lords/2016-01-14/HL5059/</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-02-02T15:41:21.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447541/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447541/answer","Hansard Extract 26 January 2016, HL 5059.docx","Hansard Extract 26 January 2016, HL 5059.docx","Reserve Forces Labour Turnover","Reserve Forces Labour Turnover","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447541/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-25","Reserve Forces: Length of Service","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what estimate they have made of the average time that reservists are members of the Armed Forces.","false","Biography information for Lord Touhig",,"Lord Touhig","HL5443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447542","Home Office","false","2016-02-02","<p>It is Home Office policy not to comment in detail on National Maritime Intelligence Centre (NMIC) capability or tasking, as to do so would, or would be likely to, prejudice national security</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2016-02-02T15:45:56.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447542/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447542/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447542/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-01-25","Territorial Waters: Surveillance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the National Maritime Intelligence Centre is providing a detailed surface picture of contacts approaching the Territorial Waters of the UK in order to enable the Border Force to intercept such vessels, and how many such interceptions there have been in the last six months.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL5444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447543","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-01","<p>The three Astute-Class submarines that have been handed over to the Royal Navy (HMS Astute, HMS Ambush and HMS Artful) were procured as a batch, so it is not possible to give an accurate assessment of the cost variation between these boats.</p><p>The National Audit Office's Major Projects Report for 2015 provides the manufacturing cost for all Astute submarines and, for Boats 4-7, explains the variation between each boat.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-02-01T16:32:20.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447543/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447543/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447543/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-25","Astute Class Submarines","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answers by Earl Howe on 8 December 2015 (HL4047 and HL4049) and on 19 January (HL4886 and HL4885), what assessment they have made of the costs of the reduction of build time of ASTUTEs.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL5445"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447544","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-01","<p>Locations for the employment of the Queen Elizabeth Class carriers will be directed by the Strategic HQ, reflecting national priorities. When deployed in the Carrier Strike or Littoral Manoeuvre roles, the composition and size of the embarked air group will be tailored to meet the required task.</p><p>The noble Lord will wish to be aware that 'F-35B Lightning II' is the designation jointly agreed by the First Sea Lord and the Chief of the Air Staff.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-02-01T16:31:49.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447544/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447544/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447544/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-25","Aircraft Carriers: Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether HMS Queen Elizabeth and HMS Prince of Wales will operate east of Suez without a F35B Sea Lightning squadron embarked.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL5446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447545","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-01","<p>Post commissioning, when deployed in the Carrier Strike or Littoral Manoeuvre role, the composition and size of the embarked air group will be tailored to meet the required task.</p><p>The noble Lord will wish to be aware that 'F-35B Lightning II' is the designation jointly agreed by the First Sea Lord and the Chief of the Air Staff.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-02-01T16:31:16.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447545/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447545/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447545/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-25","Aircraft Carriers: Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what percentage of the days at sea by HMS Queen Elizabeth and HMS Prince of Wales post commissioning will be without F35B Sea Lightning squadrons embarked.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL5447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447546","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-02-04","The National Maritime Information Centre assist with work to investigate Illegal, Unreported and Unregulated fishing around the British Indian Ocean Territory and Pitcairn. Overseas Territories are policed in a variety of ways as marine management is a devolved responsibility. In St Helena, Ascension and Tristan de Cunha a variety of surveillance and enforcement measures are deployed, including satellite monitoring, vessel tracking, short term patrols and observer coverage of fishing vessels. Potential enhancements to surveillance and enforcement requirements for the UK’s 14 Overseas Territories are being considered as part of the Government’s commitment to create a Blue Belt around these territories.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-02-04T17:04:37.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447546/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447546/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447546/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-25","British Overseas Territories: Exclusive Economic Zone","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the National Maritime Intelligence Centre is providing comprehensive surface coverage of the Exclusive Economic Zones of dependent territories to ensure wildlife and resource protection; and how those zones are policed, in particular around Tristan da Cunha, Ascension Island and St Helena.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL5448"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448496","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-28","<p>As part of our Rail Investment Strategy, the Government is investing over £700 million on infrastructure in the most congested routes in London and the South East between 2014-2019, in addition to delivering the £14.8bn Crossrail and £6.5bn Thameslink projects, which will transform east-west and north-south travel across the region.</p><br /><p>Further, our franchising programme is delivering better services. For example, bidders in the East Anglia competition will be required to deliver faster services on the Great Eastern Main Line.</p><br />","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-28T14:48:54.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448496/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448496/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448496/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-25","Railways: South East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to improve rail links in the South East.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","903310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448497","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-28","<p>We have capped regulated rail fares at the level of the Retail Price Index (RPI) for two years running, and will continue to do so for the life of this parliament.</p><br /><p>The bus market outside London is deregulated and decisions regarding setting the level of fares, is primarily a commercial matter for bus operators.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-01-28T14:55:52.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448497/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448497/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448497/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-25","Public Transport: Fares","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of recent trends in the cost of bus and rail travel.","false","Biography information for Gerald Jones","Merthyr Tydfil and Rhymney","Gerald Jones","903327"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448498","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-28","<p>We are completely committed to the reform of ticketing arrangements for rail passengers as set out in our Manifesto. We want to accelerate progress, support programmes where necessary and challenge operators to do more. A copy of the speech I made on this subject on Tuesday can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/the-death-of-the-tangerine-ticket" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/the-death-of-the-tangerine-ticket</a></p><br /> <br />","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-28T15:06:17.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448498/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448498/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448498/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-25","Railways: Tickets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress his Department has made on its plans to reform ticketing arrangements for rail passengers.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","903332"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448499","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-28","<p>The first ever electric trains are now running between Liverpool and Manchester, and Liverpool and Wigan, and the Farnworth tunnel is now open, further proof of this Government’s commitment to electrification – part of the biggest rail investment since Victorian times.</p><br />","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-28T15:01:09.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448499/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448499/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448499/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-25","Railways: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent progress his Department has made on its rail electrification programme.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","903331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448500","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-28","<p>The first ever electric trains are now running between Liverpool and Manchester, and Liverpool and Wigan, and the Farnworth tunnel is now open, further proof of this Government’s commitment to electrification – part of the biggest rail investment since Victorian times.</p><br /><p>In addition, the honourable gentleman’s constituents are already benefitting from electric trains running from Manchester Victoria, on the edge of his constituency, running into Liverpool. Network Rail’s £44m restoration of Manchester Victoria has completely transformed this station into a modern and exciting gateway to the city – part of more than £1 billion of investment in the north of England.</p><br />","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-28T15:10:11.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448500/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448500/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448500/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-25","Railways: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent progress his Department has made on its rail electrification programme","false","Biography information for Graham Stringer","Blackley and Broughton","Graham Stringer","903333"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448501","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-28","<p>Hydrogen fuel cell electric vehicles have the potential to play an important role in decarbonising road transport, alongside battery electric vehicles. Government began work with industry in 2012, in the “UK H2 Mobility” programme, to develop a roadmap on hydrogen for transport.</p><br /><p>In March last year we announced £6.6m investment in 12 initial hydrogen refuelling stations. We are working with stakeholders on options to support the wider roll-out of hydrogen in transport.</p><br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-28T16:05:02.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448501/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448501/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448501/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-25","Fuel Cells","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what support his Department is giving to encourage the use of hydrogen fuel cells in transport.","false","Biography information for John Pugh","Southport","John Pugh","903329"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446979","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-27","The background to the Government’s decision to introduce private capital into the Green Investment Bank (GIB) can be found in the policy document entitled “Future of the Green Investment Bank plc” that was published on 18 November on GOV.UK. In addition to this, the Government has also introduced provisions to the Enterprise Bill which require a report to be laid before Parliament once a decision to undertake a sale has been made. The report must set out the type of sale, the expected timescale, and the Government’s objectives for the sale.","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-01-27T17:09:08.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446979/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446979/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446979/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-22","Green Investment Bank: Privatisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will place in the Library any document which provide an evidential basis for the Government's decision to privatise the Green Investment Bank.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","23730"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446980","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-27","<p>Since May 2015 UK Trade and Investment Defence and Security Organisation (UKTI DSO) officials have met with Saudi Arabian officials from the Ministry of National Guard, Ministry of Interior, Ministry of Defence, King Abulaziz City for Science and Technology, Ministry of Municipalities and Rural Affairs, ArRiyadh Development Authority and Ministry of Foreign Affairs.</p><br />","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-01-27T17:07:11.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446980/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446980/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446980/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-22","UK Trade and Investment Defence and Security Organisation: Saudi Arabia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will publish details of UK Trade and Investment Defence and Security Organisation meetings with Saudi Arabian officials.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","23721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446981","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-02","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>There has been no formal assessment of potential risks to human rights of the Tradeshow Access Programme. However, companies using the programme are bound by UK law and exports are made in accordance with the UK’s strict export control legislation and in respect of all relevant international treaties and obligations.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-02-02T17:08:28.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446981/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446981/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446981/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-22","Tradeshow Access Programme: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what formal assessments UKTI has made of potential risks to human rights of the Tradeshow Access Programme; and what guidelines or criteria were used for those assessments.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","23747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446982","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-01-27","<p>DECC is committed to providing investors with certainty and recognises the importance of the financial markets in the energy sector. We are engaging regularly with developers and investors on how policy decisions impact their investments, both present and future.</p><br /><p>In order to protect investor confidence, DECC has made it clear that no onshore wind or solar projects already accredited and that have started to receive support under subsidy schemes will be affected by the recent regulatory changes. We have provided grace periods and exceptions to the removal of grandfathering to protect those who have already made significant financial commitments or who experience grid delays.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-01-27T14:01:33.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446982/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446982/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446982/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-01-22","Renewable Energy: Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment she has made of the effect of recent changes to wind and solar power regulations on investor confidence in the green economy.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","23760"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446983","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-28","<p>We are monitoring take up of the new steel procurement instructions and departments will be required to report back on how they have applied them to their major projects involving steel.</p><p>We will also carry out spot check investigations on a sample of projects through our Mystery Shopper service. This will give an indication of how the changes have impactedon both the UK steel industry and the number of contracts awarded to British steelmakers.</p><p>The UK steel industry supports this approach.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-01-28T15:27:21.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446983/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446983/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446983/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-22","Government Departments: Iron and Steel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment he has made of the effect that changes to procurement rules for Government contracts announced on 30 October 2015 are having on (a) the UK steel industry and (b) the contracts to British steelmakers have been awarded.","false","Biography information for Ms Angela Eagle","Wallasey","Ms Angela Eagle","23748"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446984","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-01","<p>Bullying and harassment have no place in today’s workplace environment and are unacceptable wherever they occur. The UK has a strong safety net of legislation to protect people from harassment in the workplace. This covers harassment on the grounds of sex, race, disability, religion or belief or sexual orientation and age. In addition, harassment is a criminal offence and victims have a right to damages.</p><p> </p><p>The best way to address unacceptable behaviour in the first instance is within the workplace. That’s why my Department’s supports the Health and Safety Executive Management Standards approach for work-related stress which includes a standard for relationships at work that covers unacceptable behaviour such as conflict, bullying and harassment. The Management Standards help organisations manage the causes of work-related stress in a simple and pragmatic way.</p><p> </p><p>The Advisory, Conciliation and Arbitration Service (Acas) also aims to support better employment relations by offering free impartial advice. Acas operates a nationwide telephone helpline for employers and employees, they can be contacted on: 0300 123 1100. Acas recently published new guidance addressing the need to conduct fair and thorough grievance and disciplinary investigations; and published new research seeking better solutions to deal with bullying.</p><p> </p><p>Acas also offers training and business solutions including free eLearning and advisory booklets explaining how employers and individuals can tackle and prevent bullying, ill treatment and harassment more effectively in Britain’s workplaces - raising employee motivation, attendance and productivity.</p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-02-01T15:46:21.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446984/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446984/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446984/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-22","Employment: Bullying","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department is taking to reduce the incidence of workplace bullying.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","23757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446985","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-01","<p>TDX Group were named as the private sector partner in December 2014. The contract was awarded in March 2015.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-02-01T17:03:17.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446985/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446985/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446985/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-22","Government: Debt Collection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when the decision to transfer a stake in the Debt Market Integrator to a private sector partner was announced.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","23774"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446986","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-01","<p>Student support for Higher Education in the UK is a devolved issue.</p><p> </p><p>Statistics showing the number of English applicants awarded Disabled Students’ Allowances (DSAs) are published annually by the Student Loans Company (SLC) in the Statistical First Release ‘Student Support for Higher Education in England’.</p><p><a href="http://www.slc.co.uk/official-statistics/financial-support-awarded/england-higher-education.aspx" target="_blank"><em>http://www.slc.co.uk/official-statistics/financial-support-awarded/england-higher-education.aspx</em></a></p><p> </p><p>We are only partway through the academic year 2015/16 and so published figures only provide an early indication of DSA support for the whole academic year.</p><p> </p><p>The changes being introduced in 2016/17 will apply to all students applying for DSAs for the first time from the 2016/17 academic year, and are intended to ensure that Higher Education Institutions are meeting their responsibilities to disabled students under the Equalities Act.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-02-01T15:34:41.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446986/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446986/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446986/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-22","Disabled Students' Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many people were (a) in receipt of the Disabled Students' Allowance (DSA) in 2015-16 and (b) affected by proposed changes to the DSA by constituent region of the UK.","false","Biography information for Mr Chris Leslie","Nottingham East","Chris Leslie","23766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446987","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-02","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>59 businesses have applied for Tradeshow Access Programme funding in support of their exhibiting costs at the Dubai security fair 2016. Funding will not be issued to the applicants until there is confirmation of attendance and eligibility for support. A list of supported business will be made available once they have received their funding.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-02-02T17:11:07.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446987/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446987/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446987/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-22","Tradeshow Access Programme: United Arab Emirates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, which companies received funding under the Tradeshow Access Programme to attend the Dubai security fair.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","23779"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446988","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-03","<p>Financial assistance under the Tradeshow Access Programme is only offered to companies whose products comply with the United Kingdom’s strict export control legislation and in respect of all relevant international treaties and obligations.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-02-03T17:16:15.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446988/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446988/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446988/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-22","Tradeshow Access Programme: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will it his policy not to provide financial assistance under the Tradeshow Access Programme in cases in which (a) doing so would contribute to the sale of security equipment to countries with poor human rights records and (b) that equipment could contribute to human rights abuses.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","23780"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446989","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-28","<p>No deduction has been made from Civil Service Pensionsof unmarried civil servants to meet the costs of widow and widowers' pensions in the event of some scheme members marrying.</p><p>Information on the date of marriage is not held.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","23778","2016-01-28T15:27:08.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446989/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446989/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446989/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-22","Civil Servants: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many unmarried civil servants had a deduction made from their civil service pensions in each of the last 10 years under the scheme to meet the costs of widow and widowers' pensions in the event of some scheme members marrying; and what the total value of those deductions was.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","23777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446990","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-28","<p>No deduction has been made from Civil Service Pensionsof unmarried civil servants to meet the costs of widow and widowers' pensions in the event of some scheme members marrying.</p><p>Information on the date of marriage is not held.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","23777","2016-01-28T15:27:08.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446990/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446990/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446990/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-22","Civil Servants: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many unmarried civil servants married after retirement from the civil service resulting in a subsequent claim for a widow or widower's pension from the Principal Civil Service Pension Scheme in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","23778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446991","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-01","<p>The Government committed to transforming the tax system at the March 2015 Budget. The aim is to create a system that is more effective, more efficient and easier for taxpayers based around new digital accounts.</p><p> </p><p>Instead of an onerous tax return, once a quarter businesses will update HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) from their digital records and, in most cases, little or no further entry of information will be needed.</p><p> </p><p>This does not mean quarterly tax returns. Instead, this is about making life easier for businesses – saving them time and money. These changes are a central part of a package of reforms that will save businesses £400m in administrative burdens. I also refer the honourable Member to my response of 11 January 2016 (with references <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-01-04/20876/" target="_blank">20876</a> and <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-01-05/21032/" target="_blank">21032</a>).</p><p> </p><p>Many taxpayers have told HMRC that they want more certainty over their tax bill and access to an in-year picture of their tax position. These reforms will make it easier for business to understand how much tax they owe, giving them far more certainty over their tax position, helping them budget, invest and grow.</p><p> </p><p>We will consult widely on how the new system should operate, and invite businesses to test the new tools and services, providing feedback ahead of rollout.</p><p> </p><p>We are also introducing these reforms gradually – not phasing them in fully until 2020, because we know how important it will be to give taxpayers time to adapt.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-02-01T15:41:37.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446991/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446991/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446991/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-22","Taxation: Self-assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the (a) cost to and (b) effect on small businesses and self-employed workers of the Government's plans to move from annual to quarterly digital tax reporting by 2020.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","23775"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446992","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-27","<p>Replacing maintenance grants with higher maintenance loans is putting additional cash in the hands of students to enable them to go to university. Building up from 2017-18, this is estimated to save £2.5bn a year from public sector net borrowing in steady state given expected student number growth. This change was accounted for in the Spending Review settlement for the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills. The Barnett formula was applied in the usual way.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-01-27T14:48:15.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446992/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446992/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446992/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-22","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 24 July 2015 to Question 7618, what was factored into the budget of the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills in the 2015 Spending Review as a result of the decision to end student maintenance grants in England.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","23788"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446993","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-27","<p>Following the 2015 Autumn Statement tax credit taper rates and income thresholds remain unchanged. Therefore no claimants will be affected.</p><p>The information requested is not available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-27T16:44:51.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446993/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446993/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446993/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-22","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claimants are expected to be affected by the changes to the income thresholds in tax credits and work allowances in universal credit in each year from 2015-16 to 2020-21.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","23789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446994","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-27","<p>Initial donations from the sanitary products VAT women’s charities fund totalling £5 million have been made to support The Eve Appeal, SafeLives and Women’s Aid, and The Haven. Further donations and recipients will be announced at Budget 2016, and further rounds of donations will follow at future fiscal events.</p><br /><p>Charities interested in applying should email the Treasury directly at <a href="mailto:Tampontax.Fund@hmtreasury.gsi.gov.uk" target="_blank">Tampontax.Fund@hmtreasury.gsi.gov.uk</a> stating their interest in the fund, including an overview of the nature of their proposal and the amount they are requesting. Following this they will be given further details of the bidding process and the detailed information required.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-01-27T16:12:51.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446994/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446994/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446994/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-22","Sanitary Protection: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what progress he has made on allocating money raised from VAT on sanitary products to women's groups; where that money has been allocated; and how local groups may apply for funding support.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","23768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446995","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-27","<p>The Chancellor and the Governor of the Bank of England are statutorily required to meet to discuss the Financial Stability Report (FSR), and any other matters relating to the stability of the UK financial system, as soon as is reasonably practicable after the publication of the report.</p><br /><p>At the most recent of these meetings—following the July 2015 FSR—the current account was discussed and the details of the meeting are published online by the Treasury at www.gov.uk.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","23772","2016-01-27T16:10:37.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446995/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446995/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446995/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-22","Balance of Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what meetings he has had on the growth of the current account deficit.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","23769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446996","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-27","<p>Despite narrowing in Q3 2015 to -3.7 per cent of GDP, the current account deficit remains high by historical standards. The widening in the UK current account deficit in recent years has been driven by a deterioration in the UK’s net investment income from abroad, while the trade deficit has continued to improve. The Office for Budget Responsibility expect the income account to “improve gradually over the forecast period” as the factors that have temporarily depressed the returns on the UK’s net assets are expected to recede, and the current account deficit continues to narrow to -2.1 per cent by 2020. Furthermore, the government’s plan to complete the repair of the public finances will support a gradual narrowing of the current account deficit, limiting any effect on the exchange rate, though we remain vigilant to the risks.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-27T16:09:33.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446996/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446996/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446996/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-22","Balance of Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential consequences of the current account deficit on the UK economy; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","23770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446997","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-27","<p>Despite narrowing in Q3 2015 to -3.7 per cent of GDP, the current account deficit remains high by historical standards. The widening in the UK current account deficit in recent years has been driven by a deterioration in the UK’s net investment income from abroad, while the trade deficit has continued to improve. The Office for Budget Responsibility expect the income account to “improve gradually over the forecast period” as the factors that have temporarily depressed the returns on the UK’s net assets are expected to recede, and the current account deficit continues to narrow to -2.1 per cent by 2020. Furthermore, the government’s plan to complete the repair of the public finances will support a gradual narrowing of the current account deficit, limiting any effect on the exchange rate, though we remain vigilant to the risks.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-27T15:56:55.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446997/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446997/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446997/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-22","Balance of Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of the increasing current account deficit on the UK economy.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","23771"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446998","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-27","<p>The Chancellor and the Governor of the Bank of England are statutorily required to meet to discuss the Financial Stability Report (FSR), and any other matters relating to the stability of the UK financial system, as soon as is reasonably practicable after the publication of the report.</p><br /><p>At the most recent of these meetings—following the July 2015 FSR—the current account was discussed and the details of the meeting are published online by the Treasury at www.gov.uk.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","23769","2016-01-27T16:10:37.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446998/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446998/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446998/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-22","Balance of Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he has met with representatives from the Bank of England on the current account deficit; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","23772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446999","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-27","<p>The widening in the UK current account deficit in recent years has been driven by a deterioration in the UK’s net investment income from abroad, while the trade deficit has continued to improve. The Office for Budget Responsibility expect factors that have depressed the returns on the UK’s net assets, such as the relative weakness in economic activity in the UK’s trading partners, to recede. The current account deficit is forecast to narrow to -2.1 per cent by 2020, limiting any impact on the exchange rate. Furthermore, the government’s plan to complete the repair of the public finances will support a gradual narrowing of the current account deficit.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-27T16:00:28.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446999/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446999/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446999/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-22","Balance of Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessments he has made of the effect of the level of the current account deficit on the future strength of the pound sterling.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","23773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447000","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-27","<p>Treasury Ministers and officials meet regularly with the Financial Conduct Authority to discuss relevant regulatory issues.</p><br /><p>As was the case with previous Administrations, it is not the Treasury’s practice to provide details of all such discussions.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","23739","2016-01-27T16:03:25.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447000/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447000/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447000/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-22","Financial Conduct Authority","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what meetings have taken place between officials of his Department and the Financial Conduct Authority since May 2015.","false","Biography information for Wes Streeting","Ilford North","Wes Streeting","23738"
