"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446714","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-01","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>Members invited to join the Apprenticeship Delivery Board will be high profile representatives of business sectors with a high potential for growth and representatives of organisations with a key role to play in supporting an expansion in apprenticeship starts.</p><p> </p><p>The membership will rotate with members being asked to join the Board for time limited period, before relinquishing their seat to a new member.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-02-01T15:51:46.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446714/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446714/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446714/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-21","Apprenticeship Delivery Board: Membership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what criteria were used in the selection process for members of the Apprenticeship Delivery Board announced by the Prime Minister on 18 January 2016.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","23617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446715","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-01","<p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>It will be for the Chair of the Institute for Apprenticeships, when appointed, to determine through discussions with Government and the Apprenticeship Delivery Board, how they should interact. The permanent Chair will be appointed through a public appointments process in 2016.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-02-01T15:49:07.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446715/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446715/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446715/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-21","Apprenticeship Delivery Board: Institute for Apprenticeships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how it is planned that the Apprenticeship Delivery Board will interact with the Institute for Apprenticeships.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","23618"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446716","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-26","<p><strong></strong></p><p><strong></strong></p><p>The Government has introduced provisions to the Enterprise Bill which require a report to be laid before Parliament once a decision to undertake a sale has been made. The report must set out the type of sale, the expected timescale, and the Government’s objectives for the sale.</p><p><strong></strong></p><br />","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-01-26T16:46:46.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446716/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446716/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446716/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-21","Green Investment Bank: Privatisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 19 January 2016 to Question 22689, when his Department plans to report to Parliament its detailed plans for the sale of the Green Investment Bank.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","23623"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446717","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-28","<p><strong></strong></p><p>The Skills Funding Agency is aware of the requirements of the Public Contracts Regulations which came into force in February 2015 and has processes in place to ensure that it complies with the requirements of the Regulations when procuring education and training services.</p><br />","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-01-28T17:18:13.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446717/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446717/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446717/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-21","Skills Funding Agency: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what contingency plans the Skills Funding Agency has in place to launch tenders for training contracts in 2017 open to all training providers and including current sub-contractors in the event of the introduction of the European Union rule that contracts must be fairly awarded in open tendering processes; and what discussions the Government has had with representatives of the EU on this matter.","false","Biography information for Lord Lilley","Hitchin and Harpenden","Mr Peter Lilley","23631"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446718","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-08","<p>Updates on the activities and achievements of the Apprenticeship Delivery Board will be posted on Gov.uk.</p><p> </p><p>More broadly, subject to Parliamentary approval, the Welfare Reform and Work Bill places a new duty on Government to report annually on progress towards meeting 3 million apprenticeships starts in England by 2020. This report will reconfirm Government’s commitment to that policy ambition, as well as ensuring transparency on progress.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-02-08T15:44:05.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446718/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446718/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446718/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-21","Apprenticeship Delivery Board: Parliamentary Scrutiny","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will make it his policy to provide regular updates to Parliament on the work of the Apprenticeship Delivery Board.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","23635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446719","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-01-28","<p>The Government is committed to achieving an 80% reduction in UK emissions by 2050. But we need to cut carbon whilst also cutting costs to the consumer and to the taxpayer.</p><br /><p>The Green Deal market framework has not been affected by the decision not to invest further public funds into the Green Deal Finance Company. Therefore, subject to Green Deal providers sourcing their own finance streams or a new finance provider entering the market, Green Deal providers may still write Green Deal plans and offer Green Deal finance to consumers.</p><br /><p>The changes to tax exemptions for low carbon cars in the Company Car Taxation system came into force in 2015-16. To date we have not seen any effect in take up of such vehicles as a result of these tax changes.</p><br /><p>Our assessment of the impact of the changes we are making to renewable electricity support are set out in the impact assessment published alongside each of the changes to renewables support which are available on <a href="http://www.gov.uk/decc" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/decc</a>.</p><br /><p>Lastly, the privatisation of the GIB will allow the company to increase its investments in the UK green economy. It will be able to raise more capital free from being on the Government balance sheet. It will also be free from State Aid restrictions on the green investments it can make.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-01-28T15:14:34.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446719/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446719/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446719/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-01-21","Environment Protection: Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment she has made of the effects of (a) termination of the Green Deal, (b) changes to tax exemptions for low carbon vehicles, (c) changes in support for renewable energy technology and (d) privatisation of the Green Investment Bank on levels of private sector investment in green and renewable products.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","23637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446720","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-29","<p><strong></strong></p><br /><p>In the light of this announcement, we have been discussing with the Welsh Government how we can work together to ensure a sustainable and successful future for the steel industry in Wales. Officials from the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills attended the first meeting of the Port Talbot Taskforce on 20th January, which was convened by the Welsh Government to develop plans to limit the impact of the job losses and support the industry further. The Welsh Government also wrote to my Rt hon Friend the Chancellor of the Exchequer on 19th January.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-01-29T14:58:35.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446720/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446720/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446720/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-21","Tata Steel: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what representations he has received from the Welsh Government in the last week on the announcement of job losses in South Wales by Tata Steel.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","23645"
