"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446770","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-29","<p>As of 22 January 2016, there were 287 British Service personnel serving in Iraq as part of Operation SHADER. This includes UK training teams providing training to the Iraq Security Forces and Kurdish Security Forces and UK support to various Coalition headquarters. Routine movements and minor changes in requirements mean that this number will vary over time.</p><p>For Afghanistan, I refer the hon. Member to the reply given by my noble Friend, the Minister of State in the House of Lords, the Rt Hon Earl Howe PC to the noble Lord, Lord Moonie, in the House of Lords to Question HL5150.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-01-29T14:01:56.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446770/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446770/answer","20160126_QnA_extract_on_Afghanistan.docx","20160126_QnA_extract_on_Afghanistan.docx","HL5150 - QnA extract on Afghanistan","HL5150 - QnA extract on Afghanistan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446770/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-21","Middle East: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many British servicemen are serving in (a) Iraq and (b) Afghanistan.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","23564"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446771","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-29","<p>The safety and security of Defence Nuclear Materials and the public is given the highest priority at all times. The relevant local agencies, including Police and the National Traffic Information Services, are consulted as necessary and factors such as road and weather conditions are always taken into account for all convoy movements.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-01-29T14:00:53.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446771/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446771/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446771/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-21","Nuclear Weapons: Transport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if his Department will make it his policy never to permit the transit of nuclear weapons in urban areas in hazardous weather conditions.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","23559"
